Seeing, therefore, that the beginning of the verse here is judged defective, what wonder is it that the like fault doth happen as to the number in the latter part of it, which defines the time of Saul’s reign, and that therefore, the number expressed by the evangelistS, who might 'as yet see the place entire, did differ so much from what is this day seen in our cepies‘?
